Bi$_{2}$O$_{3}$ can be found in at least six forms (Harwig, 1978; Locherer, 2011): \begin{itemize} \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B3_mP20_14_2e_3e-003}{monoclinic $\alpha$-Bi$_{2}$O$_{3}$}, the ground state, stable up to 729$^{\circ}$, \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B3_tP20_117_i_adgh-001}{tetragonal $\beta$-Bi$_{2}$O$_{3}$, $D5_{12}$}, a metastable state observed at 650$^{\circ}$C (this structure), \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A13B20_cI66_197_af_2cf-001}{body-centered cubic $\gamma$-Bi$_{2}$O$_{3}$}, another metastable phase observed at 639$^{\circ}$C, \item \href{current_web_home_dir/AB8_cF36_225_a_f-001}{face-centered cubic $\delta$-Bi$_{2}$O$_{3}$}, the stable phase from 729$^{\circ}$ up to the melting point at 824$^{\circ}$C (this structure), \item a high-pressure \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B3_hP20_159_bc_2c-001}{HP-Bi$_{2}$O$_{3}$}, and \item a second ``nonquenchable'' high-pressure structure, \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B3_hP20_186_bc_2c-001}{HPC-Bi$_{2}$O$_{3}$}. \end{itemize} ~ \vspace{-.25in} 
 The oxygen sites are occupied 18.75\% of the time.  If $z_{2} \rightarrow 1/4$, they coalesce on the (2c) Wyckoff position, and this becomes the \href{current_web_home_dir/AB2_cF12_225_a_c-001}{fluorite ($C1$) structure}. 
 Other compounds with different stoichiometries have this structure. In copper(I) iodide both the high temperature $\alpha$-CuI and the ground state $\gamma$-CuI phases are in this structure, with the copper atoms occupying 1/8 of the (32f) sites. (Keen, 1995)
